d in the trimmed version of content.','','none'),(2793,'','default','The Aggregator module is an on-site syndicator and news reader that gathers and displays fresh content from RSS-, RDF-, and Atom-based feeds made available across the web. Thousands of sites (particularly news sites and blogs) publish their latest headlines in feeds, using a number of standardized XML-based formats. For more information, see the online handbook entry for <a href=\"@aggregator-module\">Aggregator module</a>.','','none'),(2794,'','default','Viewing feeds','','none'),(2795,'','default','Feeds contain published content, and may be grouped in categories, generally by topic. Users view feed content in the <a href=\"@aggregator\">main aggregator display</a>, or by <a href=\"@aggregator-sources\">their source</a> (usually via an RSS feed reader). The most recent content in a feed or category can be displayed as a block through the <a href=\"@admin-block\">Blocks administration page</a>.','','none'),(2796,'','default','Adding, editing, and deleting feeds','','none'),(2797,'','default','Administrators can add, edit, and delete feeds, and choose how often to check each feed for newly updated items on the <a href=\"@feededit\">Feed aggregator administration page</a>.','','none'),(2798,'','default','OPML integration','','none'),(2799,'','default','A <a href=\"@aggregator-opml\">machine-readable OPML file</a> of all feeds is available. OPML is an XML-based file format used to share outline-structured information such as a list of RSS feeds. Feeds can also be <a href=\"@import-opml\">imported via an OPML file</a>.','','none'),(2800,'','default','Configuring cron','','none'),(2801,'','default','A correctly configured <a href=\"@cron\">cron maintenance task</a> is required to update feeds automatically.','','none'),(2802,'','default','<acronym title=\"Outline Processor Markup Language\">OPML</acronym> is an XML format used to exchange multiple feeds between aggregators. A single OPML document may c